a high-powered telescope,

00:00:42.680 --> 00:00:45.380 align:middle line:84%
NASA detected the
specific wavelength

00:00:45.380 --> 00:00:49.550 align:middle line:84%
unique to water molecules with
a relatively large concentration

00:00:49.550 --> 00:00:52.310 align:middle line:90%
in the sunny Clavius crater.

00:00:52.310 --> 00:00:54.200 align:middle line:90%
But don't pack your bags yet.

00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:59.690 align:middle line:10%
The concentration of water is
100 to 412 parts per million.

00:00:59.690 --> 00:01:01.910 align:middle line:10%
That's about a 12-ounce
bottle of water

00:01:01.910 --> 00:01:04.610 align:middle line:10%
per cubic meter of soil.

00:01:04.610 --> 00:01:06.710 align:middle line:84%
Compare that to
the Sahara Desert,

00:01:06.710 --> 00:01:11.030 align:middle line:84%
which has about 100 times that
amount of water in the Earth.

00:01:11.030 --> 00:01:13.190 align:middle line:84%
With such a small
amount of water,

00:01:13.190 --> 00:01:16.190 align:middle line:90%
what does this discovery mean?

