NASA's Casey Honniball
said in a statement,

00:01:18.770 --> 00:01:21.860 align:middle line:10%
"Without a thick atmosphere,
water on the sunlit lunar

00:01:21.860 --> 00:01:24.680 align:middle line:10%
surface should just
be lost to space.

00:01:24.680 --> 00:01:26.630 align:middle line:10%
Yet somehow we're seeing it.

00:01:26.630 --> 00:01:28.370 align:middle line:10%
Something is
generating the water,

00:01:28.370 --> 00:01:31.190 align:middle line:10%
